<Content>Not recommended - offers little except location There are four reasons to stay at the Sheraton in Old San Juan:-It is clean and recently refurbished.-You want to spend a day walking around Old San Juan 鈥?which is fun.-There are some interesting local restaurants within walking distance.-You are sailing from the cruise dock across the street. (But note that the Caribbean Princess and the some other large ships sometime sail from the Pan American pier, an $18.00 taxi ride though traffic to from the Sheraton.)Otherwise, this is an expensive, rather unpleasant hotel with little to recommend it.We had a 鈥渂etter鈥?room with a partial water view. With an armoire instead of a closet and a small window with a permanent wooden shade, the room seemed small and crowded. With the exception of the check in desk and a few couches, the entire lobby area has been turned over to a noisy casino. There is a hamburger restaurant on the ground floor and a typical hotel restaurant on the second floor. Given much better alternatives in the neighborhood, we saw no reason to eat at either. Internet is $10/day. If you have a laptop, try Starbucks.The dinky gym on floor 9 has two treadmills, a few trainers and a rickety universal. A rather nice compact pool area on the same floor is marred by blastingly loud music.And let鈥檚 not forget the bellman who walked down our hallway at 7:30 am Sunday morning, loudly whistling Christmas carols and slamming doors as he picked up luggage. We would not recommend this hotel. 
