<Content>Best for the area I read some of the reviews and thought it was going to be a problem. I was in Old San Juan for work so we had no choice in hotel stay. However, I was somewhat surprised. Basic rundown:Rooms: Average Hotel Room. However, if you get the suite it is better. We received a suite for half of our stay and the difference was clear. The view of the port, balcony, separate living room, bigger closet, bedroom, two television sets. Nice.Pool/Hot Tub: This was a big disappointment. The pool was dirty and small. The hot tub was basic, but did not look clean. My husband and I did not use either.Hotel Staff: They were friendly and took care of your needs upon asking. The bellman who gets your taxi does this wierd whistle call. Area: There is not a whole lot to do in Old San Juan; however I recommend the following places: -Senor Frogs (a different theme every day of the week) definatley a party spot (live band, wet t-shirt contest, women wrestling, and many other crazy things-Las Verde - the beach is about a 15 minute ride and it is beautiful-Bacardi Factory - this was not all that exciting, but the cheap liquor and free drinks were nice-Local Shopping in the square at night live bandPlaces I would skip:La Rumba - the booze cruise is really for the locals and unless you want to listen to Latin music for 2 hours I would not suggest. Although to go out on the boat for 2 hours for $10 bucks was not badLas Americans Mall - It is a nice huge mall, but it is one we have seen in the states 100x. Walking Around at night we were told by the locals to stay close to the hotel, because it is not safe at night on the weekend.Overall nice place to visit for about 2-3 days only. 
