<Content>Wyndham Old San Juan Dec 28-31, 2003 Stayed at the Wyndham Old San Juan Dec 28-31, 2003 - post cruise. I paid $120 through Priceline and met other guests who paid over $250 for a similar room. The hotel is in a great location - walking distance to the forts, shopping areas and ferry to the Bacardi factory. Its moderately clean and has a small roof top pool and an exercise room. This was my 4th stay in Puerto Rico and I expected sub-standard service that the locals dole out in larger hotels and tourist restaurants. However, I must say this place takes wins the award for rude staff. For those who want to experience the real Puerto Rico and people I recommend renting a car and driving to the small family owned hotels located all over the island. 
