<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Enjoyed our stay! We had a great time here! We had to book a room for 2 nights over the phone with the Wyndham OSJ while in an emergency situation. The hotel we had originally booked in OSJ was a bug infested hovel and we needed a nice place to stay ASAP. I called them and they were very accomadating. We walked the 4 blocks from the nightmare hotel, arriving at the Wyndham all tired, hot  sweaty. Check-in was handled very quickly by a friendly clerk. Within minutes we were up in our beautifully decorated cool room. We could not believe the difference between the Wyndham OSJ and the hovel we had just left. We even had a beautiful view of the harbor without paying extra for it. The price difference between the two hotels was only $4 a night! Unbelievable. Needless to say, we had a very nice pre-cruise stay here, and would stay here again in a heartbeat. Live music nightly out front at their patio cafe/bar. We did not eat in the hotel, wanting to sample the local resturants we had been hearing about. The casino seemed to be full of locals, but had no problems with them. We walked outside the hotel at night and did not have any problems. Saved most of our explorations of the area for daytime shopping hours. We did not try out the pool on the roof, nor the spa  gym. Had no interest in these items this trip. Harbor is across the street, Carnival ships dock just down the street from the hotel and the Love Boat docks right across the street. But you will need to take a taxi to get to the Pam American dock for RCCL ships, too far to walk. Taxi's are very easy to get and rates/prices are set. 
